[start section id="20103"]

Mr. Smallwood is a 38-year-old male with some rectal bleeding on-and-off and underwent further evaluation with a colonoscopy and was found to have a mid to upper rectal cancer.  Endoscopic ultrasound shows it to be a T3 with positive lymph nodes by cytology.  CT-scan does not show any evidence of metastatic disease.  He is now here for surgical intervention. Risks, benefits, alternatives, indications, procedure, team approach and advance directives discussed with the patient and he wishes to proceed with surgery

